HEADWORD: Perpetuation
<hw>Per*pet`u*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>perp⟦eacute⟧tuation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of making perpetual, or of preserving from extinction through an endless existence, or for an indefinite period of time; continuance.</def>  <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

